		<credit project="CfPBoK@https://slebok.github.io/cfpbok/"/>
		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2013"></a><br><code>sle2013/paper17</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2013</a> paper:</span><br><i>Mapping-Aware Megamodeling: Design Patterns and Laws</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ZinovyDiskin.html">Zinovy Diskin</a>, <a href="../profile/SaharKokaly.html">Sahar Kokaly</a>, <a href="../profile/TomMaibaum.html">Tom Maibaum</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-02654-1_18">10.1007/978-3-319-02654-1_18</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagM">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> Megamodels act as meta-level descriptions of models and mappings; the paper proposes richer, mapping-aware megamodeling constructs and principles.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4b.html"><span class="tagL">T4B: Horizontal Transformation</span></a><ul><li> The work centers on explicit mappings between models (transformations/conversions) and how they are represented and reasoned about.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagL">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It formulates “laws” and design patterns for megamodels, emphasizing principled (often formal) constraints on mapping structures and operations.
</li></ul></li></ul>
